&gt; I would love to see a language try to implement a rule where only an indented line is considered part of the previous expression.<p>Elm does this (so maybe Haskell too). For example<p><pre><code>    x = &quot;hello &quot;
     ++ &quot;world&quot;

    y = &quot;hello &quot;
    ++ &quot;world&quot; -- problem</code></pre>
